_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"19219"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Fletton & Stanground","seats":1,"turnout_pct":32.2,"results_url":"https://www.peterborough.gov.uk/council/elections/election-details","candidates":[{"n":"Christian Hogg","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":919,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"19307","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/19307/92bfcf3a-e064-44c0-bbb9-ec43627d9764.png","url":"\"https://www.peterboroughlibdems.org.uk/\""},{"n":"Maria Pinotes","p":"Reform UK","v":874,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"130136","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/130136/dda62694-fbb9-4133-b7ef-5d161bdb7b73.png"},{"n":"Andrew Johnson","p":"Labour Party","v":275,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"130135"},{"n":"Neil Seekings","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":255,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"110788","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/110788/5ab67351-c0b8-4850-905e-74fdc5228c84.png","stmt":"Dear Resident,\nI was born and raised in Stanground and have spent most of my life here. \nThis isn’t just where I live — it’s home.\nMy roots run deep here, and I understand what makes our community \nspecial.\nI started my working life as a labourer at Fletton LB1 and later built and ran my \nown software business for nearly 30 years before retiring at 60. Those years \ntaught me the value of hard work, responsibility and getting things done and \nnow I have the time and experience to give something back to the community \nthat has given me so much.\nI’m incredibly proud of our ward and the opportunities it has for the future. We \nare home to The POSH — a club that means so much to the identity of our city. \nAs a lifelong supporter, I support the campaign led by Paul Bristow to secure a \nnew multi-use stadium for Peterborough, bringing regeneration, jobs and \ninvestment to our area.\nFletton and Stanground is also at the heart of exciting developments for our city. \nThe new Cygnet Bridge will connect our ward more directly to the riverfront and \ncity centre, and residents should have a real say in shaping how that area \ndevelops.\nWe are also fortunate to have fantastic local assets such as the Green Backyard \ncommunity space and the young people’s employment hub based at the \nPeterborough Utd stadium, helping local young people gain skills and \nopportunities for the future.\nWith the right leadership and community voice, we can build on these strengths \nand make our ward an even better place to live.\nMy commitment is simple: to be a visible, hard-working councillor who listens to \nresidents and stands up for our community.\nTogether we can protect what makes Fletton and Stanground special and help \nour community thrive.\nNeil Seekings"},{"n":"Jon Lloyd","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":41,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"19268"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Fletton & Woodston","seats":1,"turnout_pct":34.5,"results_url":"https://www.peterborough.gov.uk/council/elections/election-details","candidates":[{"n":"Ed Murphy","p":"Green Party","v":1007,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"3704","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/3704-526a9070-9d49-498b-9d7b-18dcdc77140f.png","tw":"\"eddiemurphy4pcc\""},{"n":"Yvonne Claire Scarrott","p":"Reform UK","v":714,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"121214","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/121214/6a96d6d2-2b44-4c2e-b8a3-19a829e99ea5.png","tw":"\"YvonneScarrott\""},{"n":"Andy Coles","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":428,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"19264","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/19264/71e0a55d-a511-49d6-8b56-10c47763bc01.png","tw":"\"CllrAndyColes\""},{"n":"Steve Harknett","p":"Independent","v":258,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"130139","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/130139/c731af18-32ab-4eca-96c4-6eda3d12795f.png","bd":"1972"},{"n":"Harvey Woodhouse","p":"Labour Party","v":254,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"118016","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/118016/077cba48-91d7-4df2-9e80-2d6e47a1cebc.png","stmt":"Fletton and Woodston’s close-knit communities deserve a hard-working councillor that understands the local issues people are dealing with. Having spent time volunteering on warm spaces initiatives, I’ve seen firsthand how people are struggling with the cost of living, and I want to be a councillor to provide a voice in the room for people in need when decisions are made about our local services.\n\nI have first-hand experience of the issues people across Fletton and Woodston face – I first moved to Cambridgeshire after my family suffered a no-fault eviction from our home of ten years, and my experience of an invisible disability (Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome) has made me a passionate advocate for supporting disabled people to thrive.\n\nAs a caseworker for Fletton and Woodston’s local MP, I’m already supporting residents every day with a variety of issues.\n\nI have a background in animal science, and volunteer locally with the Wildlife Trust on nature conservation and environmental protection.\n\nIf elected, my key priorities for Fletton and Woodston would include focusing on improving green spaces for all, pushing for CCTV coverage of fly-tipping hotspots and lobbying the Conservative police and crime commissioner for more visible policing in the area. It would be a privilege to represent the ward – let’s restore pride in Fletton and Woodston.\n\nI’m more than happy to chat to anyone that would like to have a conversation about what I’m standing for – please just reach out.","url":"\"https://www.peterboroughlabour.org.uk/in-your-area/fletton-and-woodston/\""}],"female_count":1,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Gunthorpe","seats":1,"turnout_pct":39.7,"results_url":"https://www.peterborough.gov.uk/council/elections/election-details","candidates":[{"n":"Andrew Bond","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":1230,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"19281","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/19281/cd658903-1ca4-4593-8634-97898c49cc9a.png","url":"\"https://www.peterboroughlibdems.org.uk/\""},{"n":"Tom Rogers","p":"Reform UK","v":912,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"70589","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/70589.png"},{"n":"Andrew MacFarlaine","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":401,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129531"},{"n":"Muhammad Ahmed","p":"Labour Party","v":162,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"129530"}],"female_count":0,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":1,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":0},{"ward":"Hampton Vale","seats":1,"turnout_pct":29.3,"results_url":"https://www.peterborough.gov.uk/council/elections/election-details","candidates":[{"n":"Paul Wiggin","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":558,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129789"},{"n":"Steve Newson","p":"Reform UK","v":463,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129787","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/129787/ddd05e60-b786-49da-9ef0-5030e2e7aa32.png"},{"n":"Toqeer Ahmed Sethi","p":"Green Party","v":299