i","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":738,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"75660"},{"n":"Keith Sharp","p":"Reform UK","v":421,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"130278"},{"n":"Mohammed Munir","p":"Green Party","v":363,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"47920"}],"female_count":1,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":1,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":1,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Orton Longueville","seats":1,"turnout_pct":33.85,"results_url":"https://www.peterborough.gov.uk/council/elections/election-details","candidates":[{"n":"Philip Anthony Whitworth","p":"Reform UK","v":775,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129890"},{"n":"Jonathan Orchard","p":"Green Party","v":691,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129889"},{"n":"Nick Penniall","p":"Independent","v":502,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"67555","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/67555/ca434db4-4ae1-4bb2-84a1-649030e38a8b.png"},{"n":"Ruwan Madugalla","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":322,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"129888","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/129888/8cf37abf-ea84-4329-8fe6-d5e57aa49f71.png","stmt":"Hello, I’m Ruwan Madugalla, your local Conservative candidate for Orton Longueville Ward.\n\nI am a local resident and an NHS nurse who understands the challenges facing local families, elderly residents, and our community. I am standing because I care deeply about the area we live in and want to make a positive difference for everyone.\n\nIf elected on 7th May, my priorities will be:\n\nCleaner streets and tackling litter and fly-tipping\n\nSupporting elderly and vulnerable residents\n\nSafer communities with action on anti-social behaviour and crime\n\nListening to residents and standing up for local concerns\n\nImproving local services and protecting our neighbourhoods\n\nI believe local politics should be about people, community, and practical action  not party politics alone. I will work hard, be visible in the community, and always listen to residents.\n\nI would be grateful for your support and your vote on 7th May.\n\nRuwan Madugalla","bd":"1983"},{"n":"Olu Akinyele","p":"Labour Party","v":255,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"97205"}],"female_count":0,"male_count":5,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Orton Waterville","seats":1,"turnout_pct":42.7,"results_url":"https://www.peterborough.gov.uk/council/elections/election-details","candidates":[{"n":"Alex Bowerbanks","p":"Green Party","v":1187,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"129857"},{"n":"Stephen James Arnott","p":"Reform UK","v":897,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129855"},{"n":"Raymond Knight","p":"Independent","v":559,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"75668","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/75668/3f00d296-ced7-4572-809f-83f540f7da27.png"},{"n":"Sanjaya Dodamgoda","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":310,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129858"},{"n":"Steve Bailey","p":"Labour Party","v":174,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129856"}],"female_count":0,"male_count":5,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Park","seats":1,"turnout_pct":39.4,"results_url":"https://www.peterborough.gov.uk/council/elections/election-details","candidates":[{"n":"Murtaza Ahmed-Munir","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1009,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"110778"},{"n":"Saif Ali Yasin","p":"Labour Party","v":655,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129949"},{"n":"Tassadaq Hussain","p":"Green Party","v":648,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129948"},{"n":"Reza Behravan","p":"Reform UK","v":315,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129947"},{"n":"Beki Sellick","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":124,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"19344","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/19344-e25c32ab-3807-4b0f-9425-65556e88aa64.png","stmt":"Beki Sellick is an engineer who worked through from shopfloor to Director. Her Peterborough business advises governments and companies on innovation. Beki helps deliver sustainable transport to fight climate change, bring people together and create jobs.\r\n\r\nAs a community campaigner, Beki creates a cleaner, safer, friendlier community. She’s won grants to build connections between neighbours.  She secured more power for tenants across Peterborough, improving homes by weeding out rogue landlords.\r\n\r\nBeki rides her bike around the city where she lives and works with her family. Beki will protect our freedoms to live, love, work and study throughout a reformed EU, empowering local and national government get on with improving everyone’s lives. \r\n\r\nBeki is standing as “Liberal Democrat – To Stop Brexit”. Stopping Brexit is key to unlock our deadlocked politics and reverse the rise in Peterborough’s hate crime, isolation and poverty.\r\n\r\n'Getting Brexit done' is false: 10 more years of uncertainty would follow. Our food safety, wages and health will be forced down as we try to get trade deals.\r\n\r\nNegotiating another Brexit is false too, with more waste and divisiveness while we wait. But if the LibDems win, we can Stop Brexit before Christmas, Remain in the EU and invest the £50billion Remain Bonus in 3 things Peterborough really wants:\r\n\r\n1. building up our city economy creating more skilled jobs, focusing on implementing innovation, giving every adult £10,000 to spend on learning;\r\n\r\n2. reversing cuts with properly funded NHS and social care, police, transport and public services, targeting child poverty with free daycare from 9 months for working parents; and\r\n\r\n3. tackling the climate emergency, insulating out fuel poverty and improving well-being.\r\n\r\nBeki offers Peterborough a vote to Stop Brexit, so we can build a city and a country where every person, every community and our planet can thrive.","tw":"\"LibdemBeki\"","li":"\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/beki-sellick-b99826126\"","bd":"1968"},{"n":"Fiona Radic","p":"Independent","v":115,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"1789","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/1789/624a5bef-8b3b-45ca-8eeb-3d780abfe090.png","stmt":"ADDRESS TO VOTERS\n\nMy 2026 Address is online and can be found here: https://fionaradic.wordpress.com/2026/04/20/address-to-voters-3/","url":"\"http://fionaradic.wordpress.com/\""}],"female_count":2,"male_count":4,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Paston & Walton","seats":1,"turnout_pct":35.8,"results_url":"https://www.peterborough.gov.uk/council/elections/election-details","candidates":[{"n":"Iva Banyalieva","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1000,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129767"},{"n":"Asif Shaheed","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":714,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"19356","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/19356/52bb49ff-6e19-4804-9b0d-aca55cd5143a.png","url":"\"https://www.peterboroughlibdems.org.uk/\""},{"n":"Ryan Gallagher","p":"Reform UK","v":666,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129768"},{"n":"Mohammed Yasin","p":"Labour Party","v":186,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"129769"},{"n":"Rob Petch","p":"Your Party","v":78,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","